This is how it was done.<br>
<br>
1. Group of 6 people that needs flag goes in first and die in trial.  They zone back in to PoJ as soon as they die and wait in GY.<br>
2. Group of ELITE people goes in and finishes first wave.  After first wave, cleric clicks on all the corpse.<br>
3. Rez box apears on dead people's screen but they don't &quot;yes&quot; until the trial is over.<br>
4. When trial ends, Elite group leaves the area.  Dead bodies may disapear from the trial area but when people click on yes, they will be rezed back to trial area and able to loot marks.  <br>
<br>
Six people can get marks easy using this exploit. Well.. it doesn't work anymore.<br>
<br>
The reason they nerfed fear in PoJ:<br>
There's a bad pathing that allows people to beat on a feared mob.  When a mob is feared, it runs and at certain point, it gets stuck at one particular spot and doesn't go anywhere.  People without snare can just pound on the mob until it's dead.  This was great spot for clerics to solo.<br>
Nerfing fear in PoJ is ghey.  They should fix root of the problem and not nerf fear.<br>
